  0.4.6

  ● Disable [38;5;230mNaming/BinaryOperatorParameterName[39m because (when non-ascii method
  names are used), it incorrectly identifies them as being [38;5;230m+()[39m operator
  overrides (overly aggressive)

  0.4.5

  ● Disable [38;5;230mNaming/AsciiIdentifiers[39m for the same reason as mentioned below in
  0.4.4 (specifically to allow programs written in non-Latin languages to define
  identifiers)

  0.4.4

  ● Disable [38;5;230mNaming/MethodName[39m cop. While [38;5;230msnake_case[39m is the conventional way to
  name a Ruby method, the cop is too restrictive in that it also prevents
  non-ASCII characters from being included in method names

  0.4.3

  ● Improve output of the todo feature

